                                        <h4 class="mbr-timeline-title mbr-fonts-style mbr-pb-2 display-2">Saltillo Tile (Spanish Clay Tiles)</h4>
                                        <p class="mbr-timeline-text mbr-fonts-style display-7">For thousands of years terracotta tiles have been used by mankind as floor and wall coverings. Nowadays, despite the huge technological advances in ceramics, Mexican hand-made terracotta floor tiles are still some of the most beautiful and sought-after building materials among architects, builders, designers, and consumers.
<br>
<br>Saltillo tile is highly porous and soaks in liquid easily. If not properly sealed and maintained, the tile can become discolored, worn down, and eventually require replacement. You should periodically test the seal by putting a few drops of water on the tile in various places. If the water is absorbed, then another coat of sealer should be applied. Different types of sealers can provide different finished looks. For example, a glossy sealer would provide a shiny, wet-look, while a penetrative sealer would allow the natural look of your beautiful tiles to remain.
<br>
<br>JP Floor Care is well-versed in the delicate handling required by Saltillo Tile, and can provide such services at Spanish Tile refinishing, resealing, and if required, Spanish Tile re-coloring.</p>
