                                        <h4 class="mbr-timeline-title mbr-fonts-style mbr-pb-2 display-2">Terrazzo</h4>
                                        <p class="mbr-timeline-text mbr-fonts-style display-7">Terrazzo is an extremely unique style of flooring and, either cement-based or epoxy-based, Terrazzo is beautiful and adds a distinct look to any space. The epoxy or cement is mixed with an aggregate of some sort to produce that beautiful and familiar terrazzo look. This aggregate can be many types of materials including: marble aggregate blends, mother-of-pearl and abalone shell, glass, porcelain, concrete, or metal. Shapes and medallions can be fabricated and inset during the installation of the terrazzo, to provide another unique finish.
<br>
<br>Of course, like any floor, maintenance is required. Contact with alkalies or acids, such as certain chemical cleaners, can deteriorate the bonding agents used in the terrazzo. Cracking and deterioration is the most common form of failure. If a large portion of the flooring must be replaced due to cracking, the damaged section must first be removed, after which the structural subsurface will be examined. Replacement terrazzo must achieve a continuous look by having the same color marble chips, or other aggregate as the rest of the floor.</p>
